caption:
Table 1: Ablation results on KITTI3D with 2D detection 
networks, AP| R40 scores.

Table 2: Results on KITTI3D when using p 2D or p 3D = p 3D|2D p 2D as the final confidence score to rank predictions. In addition, 
we report the performance when the confidence is sampled from a uniform distribution.

Table 3: AP| R40 scores on KITTI3D: ablation results (white background), test set results of SOTA (grey background) and 
ours (green background).
Table 4: AP| R11 scores on KITTI3D: test set results of SOTA (grey background) and ours (green background).

Table 5: AP| R11 scores on KITTI3D (0.7 IoU threshold): Ablation results (white background), val set results of SOTA (grey 
background).
Table 6: Results on the classes Pedestrian and Cyclist on the KITTI3D validation set (0.5 IoU threshold).

Table 7: Performance comparison for results on category 
car in nuScenes dataset [2]. Top row: LiDAR-based Point-
Pillar results (listed for completeness). Bottom: Available 
OFTNet results vs. MonoDIS.
